cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as morphological reinflection. The use of recurrent neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper's focus on improving performance through the use of unlabeled data could place it in the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
